		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31212829">It depends entirely on who the translation is made for. If it's an official localisation for a product that westerners are likely to find appealing (i.e. Attack on Titan, Vagabond or even the Persona 4 game) then honorifics are out-of-place and will alienate and limit the audience. If what's being translated lacks mainstream western appeal and is targeted largely at otaku (the OreImo anime or an eroge, for example), then it makes sense to keep the honorifics; the audience will understand their meaning and implications. Non-otaku will not.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://img541.imageshack.us/img541/6581/v46o.png" /><!--center--></div></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
