		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31242597">I generally prefer omitting honorifics as much as possible. Most things can be said without them and the lowest common denominator for translations is usually the casual viewer who might get lost in too much japanesiness. Of course, if a translation is aimed specifically at nerds, honorifics should be kept. The fansubs who care about their audience often include 2 subtitle tracks in their releases to 'please' everyone.<br />
