		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31277379">I very much prefer honorifics for the same reason nil said, because it loses less information.  Honorifics-English is not a terrible language, and it's one I'm comfortable reading in at this point.  For me, it doesn't lose flow and is the best solution.<br />
<br />
Omitting the honorifics entirely is probably better for people who aren't used to Honorifics-English or simply prefer normal english.<br />
<br />
Anything that constantly puts a title in front of someone's name ("Hey, bro Nil!") breaks immersion constantly for me, and I will immediately find another sub.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=2913"> <img src="http://i.imgur.com/Cci6bQq.png" /> </a><!--center--></div></div></td>
